Thank you MoMa for bringing art and film together as a force for our common humanity - what a beautiful night!
Snipets from Guillermo Del Torro speech last night at MoMA. He moved the room to tears 
Purpose of art to cronicle what we know 
Form of art occupies itself with the impossible. Land of parable and fable and these are the ones I have chosen. 
Only way you can be loved is to give your love for who you are
Wear imperfections as a badge of honor. Why I love monsters and why film has saved my life so many times. 
Exist in land beyond words, with sound and images.’
Followed beckoning of things I cannot name and aspire to ideas to be faithful - to birth monsters and find truth.
In this quest joined again to be with MoMA with Pinocchio - Presents a creature judged as an outsider —
embrace each other in our imperfection and love each-other
Fantasy allows us to grasp ideas and concepts we cannot imagine or encompass 
Duty of art is mystery. Power of art to heal us and make us whole 
We seek each other and find each other as are common spirit 
Pursue art -we break first 7 years and then rest of life to make whole the scars as beautiful 
#guillermodeltoro is a creative genius and beautiful human being. Honored to witness his words and the love so palpable in the room last night for him and what he has created for the world. Thank you! #art #film# MoMA

Great times in Jamaica - went to #stushinthebush which is the mountain home of Lisa and Chris Binn’s in Freehill, St Ann - an elegant and genius inspired plant based dining experience with a stellar garden and Eden like fruit trees. Gets you in in touch with food on an earth level of beauty and every flavor is impeccably thought out and served with locally crafted pottery. It is all done with the utmost intentionality- everything there is an expression of love - this is the future of food, the future of living in relation to our bountiful earth, this is love reimagined with gentleness and creativity. An amazing day and hope a destination for people to imagine how we can live with love beauty creativity and explosion of color and flavor and learning from plant wisdom that is all around us. #jamaica #love #plantwisdom #beauty #plantbased #vegan #collectively 
#stannsjamaica @musesmoment @gdr_shantaram @stushinthebush @jacanawellness @musingsmagazine #questlove #

It is an immense honor to be a Judge of the @TOMFORD Plastic Innovation Prize, the only global competition focused on sourcing and scaling biologically based and degradable alternatives to traditional thin-film plastic made from fossil fuels. Over the past year, I have been on a journey with my fellow Judges and the Scientific & Technical Advisory Board members to review the Finalists’ material testing data, vet their ability to scale, and trial sample materials to gauge whether they meet industry standards. This work requires systemic change, which would not be possible without a diverse set of stakeholders. 

Thank you to my fellow Judges: @tomford, @keyinfluencer, @doncheadle, #AudreyChoi (@morgan.stanley), @liviafirth (@ecoage), @john_john_florence, #DrAndrewForrest (@minderoofoundation), #EllenJackowski (@mastercard), #JoeKudla (@vuoriclothing), #PhillipSarofim (@trousdaleventures), @stevenkolb (@cfda), @stellamccartney, #LizRodgers (@nike), @trudiestyler, #TomSzaky (@terracycle), @s.a.s.k.i.a.v (@rothys), @danniwashington (@bigblueandyou), @melatiwijsen (@youthtopia.world).

And to our Scientific & Technical Advisory Board: @tombbien (@plasticodyssey), #OliverCampbell (@delltech), #DrMarcusEriksen (@5gyres), #AndyJohnson (@roq.us), @fabien_laurier, #DrErinMeyer (@seattleaquarium), #EllieMoss, #DrRamaniNarayan (@michiganstateu), #JamieRowles (@foundersfactory), #JRSiegel, #BobTeasley (@millerknoll)

Visit PLASTICPRIZE.ORG and follow @LonelyWhale to find out more.

Spectacular nature in Patagonia and flying over glaciers and snow fields that took my breath away. The Torres Del Paine region is so beautiful and seeing these glaciers and the millions of years of geological formations followed by glaciers made in past 12k years makes one pause to think how fleeting our time on earth is. Also how we must protect the places we love. #protectwhatisprecious #beauty #nature #love #glaciers #patagonia
